<Screen title="Ascii Animation Lab">
  <Section title="Signal">
    <Text>The new AsciiAnimation component plays natively in the curses runtime.</Text>
    <Text>Use this screen to judge frame cadence, box layout, clipping, and whether motion still feels calm inside a 79-column canvas.</Text>

    <AsciiAnimation label="Signal" fps="6">
      <Frame>
      +---------+
      |*        |
      |  erza   |
      +---------+
      </Frame>
      <Frame>
      +---------+
      |   *     |
      |  erza   |
      +---------+
      </Frame>
      <Frame>
      +---------+
      |      *  |
      |  erza   |
      +---------+
      </Frame>
    </AsciiAnimation>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Checklist">
    <Text>Check whether the animation block stays visually stable while frames change.</Text>
    <Text>Check whether page mode movement, section mode scrolling, gg, and G still feel clean while the animation is ticking.</Text>
    <Link href="https://erza.ryangerardwilson.com/labs/">Open the hosted labs page</Link>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Controls">
    <Text>Header mode uses a horizontal strip of section headers. h and k move to the previous header. j and l move to the next header. Press Enter to focus the current section.</Text>
    <Text>Section mode uses j/k line by line, and Ctrl+D/Ctrl+U for half-page moves.</Text>
    <Text>gg and G jump to the first or last section or line. Esc returns to the header strip. Backspace goes back. ? shows shortcuts. q exits cleanly.</Text>
  </Section>
</Screen>
